step.simpara:
Install &app-xcode;
You can install &app-xcode; from the App Store or install the much smaller Xcode command line tools by running sudo xcode-select --install from a Terminal.app prompt.
if it is not installed. It contains devel tools, which are required by CPAN to build and test the needed &app-fq; modules.

tip.para:
With gnc-fq-dump you can check symbols faster than from &app;
          if an error occurs during the retrieval with &app;. This might save you from running
          &app; with debug logging enabled while checking a nonworking symbol.
